-- Impresa Says SIC Television Audience Share Dropped in August
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-09-04T10:47:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-04/impresa-says-sic-television-audience-share-dropped-in-august.html
Impresa SGPS SA (IPR)  said television
station SIC’s share of the Portuguese television audience
dropped in August.  SIC had a share of 20.2 percent in August, the company said
in a statement on its website today. In July, SIC’s audience
share reached 20.6 percent, Impresa spokesman Jose Freire said
in an e-mailed statement.  The broadcaster had the second-biggest audience share among
 Portugal ’s four open-air channels last month, behind TVI
television channel, Impresa said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
 halmeida5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jerrold Colten at 
 jcolten@bloomberg.net  